txSpace Installation
------------------------

by Phil Christensen
phil@bubblehouse.org

Requirements for Server:
* Python                  (http://www.python.org)
* Twisted                 (http://www.twistedmatrix.com)
* Nevow                   (http://divmod.org/trac/wiki/DivmodNevow)

Requirements for Client:
* Firefox                 (http://www.mozilla.com/firefox)
* Safari 3.0+             (http://www.apple.com/safari)

Quick Start
------------
Server:

1.) Prerequisites:
    - download and install Twisted
    - download and install Nevow
2.) Install:
    - add the txspace source directory to PYTHONPATH, OR
    - create a txspace.pth file in site-packages, containing
      the path to the source directory,  OR
    - drop the txspace folder into site-packages

3.) twistd -n txspace
    (omit the -n to daemonize)

When the server is shutdown, it saves its state in a file in the current
directory called "universe.xml.shutdown". When it starts up, it looks for this
file, and, if found, renames "universe.xml" to "universe.xml.bak" and
"universe.xml.shutdown" to "universe.xml", and loads the resulting file.

Client:

1.) Connect to http://localhost:8080
2.) Login with u/p: wizard/wizard